        "summary": "Imam Ali (AS) teaches that one should adopt a courageous mindset by considering distant goals as near and difficult tasks as easy. He emphasizes the doctrine of divine decree (qadar): no human strategy, whether weak or powerful, can change what Allah has allotted to a person. This teaching was delivered to encourage believers to rely on Allah rather than on their own cunning, reflecting the Shia emphasis on tawakkul (reliance on God) alongside personal effort.",
